Text.Value: Chk. Clearly our schooling is not what it used to be.
There are more rudimentary methods of extraction, if you find our technology intimidating.
You aren't the first istik to require my treatment - though you're the most lucid by some margin.

EditorData.NodeContext: trying to sound casual, secretly excited. "treatment" = fatally experimented on

Text.Value: Though I will admit, it's fascinating that you're still able to lie at this stage of infection.

EditorData.NodeContext: curiosity getting the best of her

Text.Value: A day or two. They seem to be fine so far.
If not, I question your choice of 'friends'.
Infected, and yet capable of maintaining a falsehood. How unusual.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: She's been waiting for you to come clean.

Text.Value: Not me personally, but my friend does. I'm trying to find a way to help them.
And you expected charity from us?
A facile achievement for those who know so little to begin with.
I can only deduce... you have a parasite of your own.
It will relieve you of the specimen lodged in your cerebral cortex. What else?

EditorData.NodeContext: knows it will kill the player, amused by their suspicion

Text.Value: I'd prefer Lae'zel to speak on my behalf.
I lied, it's me. I'm the one with the tadpole.
I have a tadpole of my own needs removing. Can you help with that?
I have first-hand knowledge. I'm infected.
Intestinal colouration consistent with samples 231 to 259.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [CHOICES] Doctor zooms the machine's lens in on the body of the dissected tadpole.
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: She zooms the machine's lens in on the body of the dissected tadpole.

Text.Value: Lae'zel, is it? Fine - and be quick. My work is of vital import.
Go to the zaith'isk. I will ensure you are cured.

EditorData.NodeContext: Excited - this is an exciting scientific prospect

Text.Value: First the nautiloid's arrival, then the ghaik swarming around Moonrise...
Tell her of the True Souls you've encountered.
Thanks for that. Learn something new every day.
Best not to delay. They may soon be beyond even my capabilities to save.
All right, I'll go fetch them.
Longer than you'd expect ceremorphosis to take. And with none of the symptoms.
I am Lae'zel of K'liir. I have come to be purified.
Not yet.
Fascinating. So you're conscious of your infection, but showing no signs of cerebral impairment.
Much like your decision to seek aid from us. The infestation at Moonrise has created strange bedfellows indeed.
Still, you appear to be functioning far beyond the capacity of others I've observed in your condition. How fascinating.

EditorData.NodeContext: curiosity getting the best of her

Text.Value: Tell me, what is your understanding of ceremorphosis?
Are you the 'friend' with the tadpole problem?

EditorData.SFXTags: psionic effect when tadpole floating at the mircoscope
EditorData.VFXTags: psionic effect when tadpole floating at the mircoscope

Text.Value: So you are not an idiot. But nor are you an intellectual.
Is that so? Conscious of the tadpole's presence, yet able to pretend otherwise. Fascinating.
If you would prefer another extraction method, kin, you have only to ask.
Either your tadpole is special, or you are. We must find out which.

EditorData.NodeContext: Excited - this is an exciting scientific prospect

Text.Value: What are you talking about?
Is that so? Dishonesty towards your superiors is an ill-advised behaviour.
Unless you have anything new of your own to share, I must get back to my sample. It's drying out.
It sounds like they've discovered a way to exist in a state of suspended ceremorphosis.
Tell how you vanquished the tadpoled Absolutists in Moonrise Towers.
Do you have a question or are you just going to stand there gawking?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext:
She addresses the player without turning around. 

She turns at the end of her question to see the player's response

Text.Value: You do not gain true knowledge by demanding it of others. It must be earned.
If your friend is not capable of asking me directly, I see no reason to get involved.
Guessing is an idiotic habit. Theorise. Postulate. Deduce. Never guess.

EditorData.NodeContext: pet peeve, can't help but correct you

Text.Value: Vertical incision from pineal eye to end of notochord.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [CHOICES] Doctor is conducting an autopsy on a mindflayer tadople. She uses her hands to psionically twist the orientation of the tadpole in the sphere that holds it.
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext:
The doctor is leaning forward, peering into a microscope. She is conducting an autopsy on a mindflayer tadople using the gith medical device. 
She uses her hands to psionically twist the orientation of the tadpole in the sphere that holds it.
EditorData.InternalNodeContext: She is absorbed in her work and doesn't react to the player's entry into the room. She knows they're there, but she's more interested in her work than them.
EditorData.SFXTags: psionic effect when moving the tadpole at the miroscope
EditorData.VFXTags: psionic effect when moving the tadpole at the miroscope

Text.Value: Most of our kin find such work rather tedious. I wonder - what makes you so curious?

EditorData.NodeContext: pleased to have had the opportunity to pontificate

Text.Value: Ah. Friendship. A curious burden I confess I have no interest in carrying.

EditorData.NodeContext: As though "friendship" is a phenomenon to be observed

Text.Value: Operational? It is exemplary. I maintain it myself.
The stupidity encouraged on this plane never ceases to amaze me. Listen carefully.
You've spent too much time with istiks, kin.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Focus on the doctor's reaction here, one of incredulity

Text.Value: You have my thanks for these observations of yours. It seems you have a scientist's eye after all.
Chk. I am no teacher.
Actually... Maybe I'll come back later.
A few days? I stopped counting when I ran out of fingers.
Chk. I see you're somewhat familiar with the material. Though hardly up to date.
I have a confession. I've been tadpoled, and I need help.
The zaith'isk is our last means of defence. It is used for the removal of illithid tadpoles.
Chk. Curiosity without toil is like a broken viewing glass: unfocused and incapable of insight.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: She considers your intellect far beneath her, but is prepared to entertain the possibility that she's wrong.

Text.Value: You have my thanks.
As you wish.

EditorData.NodeContext: smug, knows that granting this request will kill the player

Text.Value: If you require treatment, take a seat, kin. Or do you have a question?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext:
She addresses the player without turning around. 

She turns at the end of her question to see the player's response

Text.Value: Wait here. I'll require some assistance.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: She's lying - she's actually going to fetch the guards.

Text.Value: Come now, no need to be shy. I assure you I'd be delighted to help this 'friend' of yours.
Look, I haven't told you everything. I'm infected...
Too long. Just get this thing out of me.
Give your observations of the tadpoled Absolutists in Moonrise Towers.
I suspected as much. Though I am fascinated that you've retained the ability to lie about it.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: She was waiting for you to come clean.
EditorData.NodeContext: curiosity getting the best of her

Text.Value: I see you have some knowledge of the process.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: She knows the 'friend' is really you. You're the one who's infected.

Text.Value: Your assumption is correct. My experiments have been vital in supporting our queen's efforts against the ghaik.
Let's see what knowledge your labours have borne so far.
And the zaith'isk is?
I'm not familiar with the term. What's a zaith'isk?
Lie down on the zaith'isk, and your troubles will be over.
What are you hoping to learn from dissecting that thing?
You appear to have somatic knowledge of the process, and yet you remain in possession of your cerebral faculties.

EditorData.NodeContext: holding back some excitement - this is genuinely new territory. As though making a study of the player

Text.Value: I am Lae'zel of K'liir. I come to be purified.
Incredible.
What a bizarre display. And yet, surprisingly accurate.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Focus on the doctor's reaction here, one of incredulity
EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Her curiosity gets the better of her - she is thinking out loud.

Text.Value: Merely curious. You seem an expert on the subject.
What does the zaith'isk do?
Relate your 'findings'. Use lots of long, complicated words.
If this friend is kin, their cowardice does little to earn my assistance.
Your knowledge betrays a closer experience than you let on. You're infected.
Very good - you've grasped the basic definition. If I ever misplace my dictionary, I'll know who to ask.
Only a powerful magic would be able to maintain such a stasis, but the Absolutists we've encountered showed no such ability.
A shame. I had hopes for you, istik.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Genuinely disappointed - she's starved of a good intellectual jousting session.

Text.Value: They won't stay that way.
Tell me, how long has your friend been infected?
Your gratitude is unnecessary. The procedure brings its own rewards.
Chk. I have no desire to teach, though your request is understandable.
Are you the ghustil? I've been infected and require purification.
True curiosity does not demand answers - it finds them for itself.
Chk. If you aren't here for treatment, then get out of my infirmary.
Hmm. A sign that your cognitive abilities are not so robust as they appear.
You were interested in the zaith'isk.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [CHOICES] *DUPE* [Doctor] she is conducting an autopsy on a mindflayer tadople. She has her back to the player. The doctor is peering into the mircoscope while poking it with a scalpel
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The doctor is conducting an autopsy on a mindflayer tadople. She has her back to the player. She talks over her shoulder to them.
EditorData.InternalNodeContext: She knows they player is there, but she's more interested in her work than them.
EditorData.SFXTags: psionic effect when tadpole floating at the mircoscope
EditorData.VFXTags: psionic effect when tadpole floating at the mircoscope

Text.Value: Every fibre, every sinew of your being is torn apart and reformed into the repugnant flesh of a ghaik, or 'illithid'. That is ceremorphosis.
Leave.
Why do you want to know?
You are infected, but showing no signs of cerebral impairment? Fascinating.
You are a unique specimen. All right, my curiosity is piqued.
It will be worth it. I assure you.
Yes, what is it?

EditorData.AnimationTags: [CHOICES] *DUPE* [Doctor] she is conducting an autopsy on a mindflayer tadople. She has her back to the player. The doctor is peering into the mircoscope while poking it with a scalpel
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The doctor is conducting an autopsy on a mindflayer tadople. She has her back to the player.
EditorData.InternalNodeContext: She is absorbed in her work and doesn't react to the player's entry into the room. She knows they're there, but she's more interested in her work than them.
EditorData.SFXTags: psionic effect when tadpole floating at the mircoscope
EditorData.VFXTags: psionic effect when tadpole floating at the mircoscope

Text.Value: Come back when you've worked these airs out of your system.
My friend is infected - I'm looking for a way to help them.
Stare blankly at her.
Bring them here, and you'll have a live demonstration of what the zaith'isk can do.

EditorData.NodeContext: excited at the prospect of using the zaith'isk, knows the zaith'isk will kill them

Text.Value: Well then?
Bring them here for purification. I will be waiting.

EditorData.NodeContext: excited at the prospect of using the zaith'isk, knows the zaith'isk will kill them

Text.Value: I'm not infected. I'm asking for a friend.
It was me all along - I'm the one who's infected.
Leave.

EditorData.stateContext: Doctor has back to player, bent forward to peer into a microscope

Text.Value: So, they are gathering. And in a state of suspended ceremorphosis.
Is that thing's host still alive?
You must be desperate, to seek my aid.

EditorData.NodeContext: obervational, not too smug or opportunistic at this point

Text.Value: Yes, can you help me get rid of it?
The specifics are... complicated. It is not a comfortable process, but a necessary one.
Go on. You know what we require.
The apparatus at the top of those stairs. Quickly now - time is of the essence.
Fine. I'll leave you to it then.
To be expected. We each have our weapons to wield. Some are sharper than others.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: With no disrespect, but it's clear she considers her craft (science) superior to yours.

Text.Value: Must you keep bothering me? If you have questions, read a book.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [CHOICES] Doctor is conducting an autopsy on a mindflayer tadople. She has her back to the player. The doctor is peering into the mircoscope while poking it with a scalpel
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The doctor is conducting an autopsy on a mindflayer tadople. She has her back to the player.
EditorData.InternalNodeContext: She is absorbed in her work and doesn't react to the player's entry into the room. She knows they're there, but she's more interested in her work than them.
EditorData.SFXTags: psionic effect when tadpole floating at the mircoscope
EditorData.VFXTags: psionic effect when tadpole floating at the mircoscope

Text.Value: The tadpole is a parasite. Once it consumes enough of your brain matter, it instigates an excruciating transformation.
Is that machine a zaith'isk? Is it operational?
I've been told someone here knows how to remove tadpoles. I'm guessing that's you.
Is your zaith'isk operational?
Longer than you'd expect ceremorphosis to take. And with none of the symptoms.
Still, I would not withhold aid if it furthers our collective efforts against the ghaik.
I'm analysing changes in the worm's digestive tract following consumption of cerebral matter.
It's the seven day process by which an illithid tadpole eats away the host's brain and takes control of its body.
A very specific question, one that speaks of a more personal motivation for asking.

EditorData.NodeContext: logical, a bit smug - she's already figured out you're infected

Text.Value: I have waited long for this.
Is that so? Then of course, you will be treated first. Lie down when you're ready.

EditorData.NodeContext: with a smile - she knows the treatment will kill you

Text.Value: Have you brought your friend?

EditorData.SFXTags: psionic effect when tadpole floating at the mircoscope
EditorData.VFXTags: psionic effect when tadpole floating at the mircoscope

Text.Value: Now go, continue your education elsewhere. You've delayed my work long enough.
Though - you are like nothing I've seen before. You remain lucid, when you should have succumbed.

EditorData.NodeContext: wheels starting to turn - she's going to experiment on you

Text.Value: I've got a tadpole of my own. I was hoping you could remove it.
I'm reporting here for tadpole extraction, as protocol demands.
I require your assistance in removing a tadpole.
Tell me, how long have you been infected?
Nothing your kind is capable of understanding.

EditorData.NodeContext: a statement of fact - not intended to be an insult

Text.Value: Your presence is not welcome here, k'chakhi.
What do you hope to gain from dissecting the ghaik spawn?
I shouldn't have said anything. It's not my place.
Few of our kin understand that wars can be fought with science, as well as swords.
Perhaps, perhaps not. Let the istik with you speak, and I will decide what respect you are owed.
If it's an education you seek, go to the training room. I'm sure the sa'varsh will be happy to oblige.
Well you certainly have a flair for something.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Focus on the doctor's reaction here, one of incredulity

Text.Value: Unfortunately, yes.
Mime every disgusting stage of transformation into a mind flayer.
I've got a tadpole needs removing. Can you help me?
The better question is - what brings an istik to my infirmary?
What will the zaith'isk do to them?
Cursed is the day that even we become ghaik incubators.
You'll be aware then, that your friend is on borrowed time.
What will the zaith'isk do?
Please, explain it to me.
We carry ghaik tadpoles, and have done so for countless days - yet we show no symptoms. We must enter the zaith'isk.
So, they were gathering. And somehow doing so in a state of suspended ceremorphosis.
I am a Child of Gith, not discarded rat-flesh. Am I not due your respect?
I'm simply keen to learn. And you seem a favourable teacher.
I've never seen one up close. And you seem a favourable teacher.
Leave.
But I've more interest in substance than... whatever it is you're trying to offer me.
Fine, you want the truth? I'm infected and I'm trying to find a cure.
Report the details of your own infection, as protocol dictates.
Well, whatever matter your skull contains, it clearly isn't cerebral in nature. Ceremorphosis is no threat to you.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: awkward beat on the player staring at the doctor

Synopsis: The player speaks to the doctor and can ask to get their tadpole removed. They can then agree to step into the device to be 'cured', or refuse and have the doctor try to leave and get the guards.
